          <h1 id="privacy">Privacy Policy</h1>
          <p>Effective Date: April 29, 2025</p>

          <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
          <p>My Car Quote ("we", "our", "us") is operated by My Car Quote Limited , a private limited company 
            registered in the United Kingdom under company number 16416376 with its registered office at 
            Manifold Way, Wednesbury, WS10 0GB. We provide an online platform for Customers to request 
            vehicle repair Quotes from independent Bodyshops.</p>

          <h2>2. What Information We Collect</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Job-related data: name, email address, phone number, postcode, vehicle details through uploaded images</li>
            <li>Quote interactions: quote views, selection of a Bodyshop</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>3. Lawful Basis for Processing</h2>
          <p>We process personal data based on the following legal grounds:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Contractual necessity – to provide the service you request</li>
            <li>Legitimate interests – to improve service performance and user experience</li>
            <li>Consent – for optional communications and marketing</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>4. How We Use Your Information</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Facilitate the submission of your Job and delivery of Quotes</li>
            <li>Enable communication with a selected Bodyshop</li>
            <li>Process secure payments</li>
            <li>Send service updates and status notifications</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>5. Data Sharing and Third Parties</h2>
          <p>We do not sell your data. Your data is only shared with Bodyshops after you choose to unlock Quote details. 
            We work with trusted service providers to process payments, support platform security, and enable core platform features. 
            These providers only access the minimum data required to perform their function under strict confidentiality agreements.</p>

          <h2>6. International Data Transfers</h2>
          <p>If your data is transferred outside the UK or EEA, we ensure appropriate safeguards are in place such as Standard Contractual Clauses 
            approved by relevant authorities or other lawful transfer mechanisms under UK GDPR.</p>

          <h2 id="cookies">7. Cookies</h2>
          <p>We use cookies to support platform functionality and performance. 
            Non-essential cookies are only enabled with your consent. 
            See <a href="#cookies">Cookies Policy</a> for details.</p>

          <h2>8. Data Retention</h2>
          <p>We retain personal data only as long as needed to fulfil our services and comply with legal obligations.
            Completed or inactive Jobs are removed from our system after 30 days, with minimal metadata retained securely for audit and record purposes.</p>

          <h2>9. Your Rights</h2>
          <p>Under UK data protection law, you have the right to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Access the personal data we hold about you</li>
            <li>Correct or update inaccurate information</li>
            <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
            <li>Withdraw consent where processing is based on consent</li>
            <li>Object to processing based on legitimate interests</li>
            <li>Data portability for information you provided</li>
            <li>Lodge a complaint with the UK Information Commissioner’s Office (ICO)</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>10. Data Security</h2>
          <p>We implement appropriate technical and organisational measures to protect your data. 
            All data is encrypted during transmission. We do not store payment card details on our platform.</p>

          <h2>11. Business Transfers</h2>
          <p>In the event of a merger, acquisition, or asset sale, personal data may be transferred to the acquiring entity under the same terms of this policy.</p>

          <h2 id="bodyshop">12. Bodyshop Data Collection and Use</h2>
          <p>When a Bodyshop registers on our platform, we collect the following personal and business data:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Business name and trading details</li>
            <li>Contact name and email address</li>
            <li>Phone number and postcode</li>
            <li>Quotes submitted and job interactions</li>
            <li>Verification status and admin approvals</li>
          </ul>

          <p>This data is used to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Enable login and account management</li>
            <li>Filter jobs based on location</li>
            <li>Display quotes to Customers once payment is made</li>
            <li>Notify Bodyshops of relevant jobs and selections</li>
            <li>Maintain platform security and service records</li>
          </ul>

          <p>Bodyshop data is stored securely and only accessible by platform administrators. 
            We do not sell or share Bodyshop data for external marketing purposes.</p>

          <p>Bodyshops may request access, correction, or deletion of their data at any time by emailing <strong>office@mcquote.co.uk</strong>. 
            Deleting an account may result in loss of access to the platform and its services.</p>

          <h2>13. Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect legal or operational changes. 
            Updates will be published here with revised dates.</p>

          <h1 id="terms">Terms & Conditions</h1>
<p>Effective Date: April 29, 2025</p>

<h2>1. Introduction</h2>
<p>These Terms & Conditions (“Terms”) govern your use of the My Car Quote platform. 
  By accessing or using this website, you agree to these Terms. If you do not agree, you must not use our service.</p>

<h2>2. Our Service</h2>
<p>My Car Quote is an online platform that allows vehicle owners (“Customers”) to receive repair Quotes from 
  local independent garages (“Bodyshops”). We are not a repair provider or insurance broker. We do not guarantee, 
  endorse, or manage the services or quotes provided by Bodyshops.</p>

<h2>3. User Responsibilities</h2>
<p>All users must provide accurate and honest information. 
  Customers must not submit misleading claims or false uploads. 
  Bodyshops must only submit professional, fair quotes. 
  Misuse of the platform may result in account restriction or removal.</p>

<h2>4. Quotes and Payments</h2>
<p>Quotes submitted by Bodyshops are non-binding until direct engagement. 
  Customers can pay a small fee to unlock full Bodyshop contact details. 
  This payment is non-refundable. 
  My Car Quote does not facilitate or guarantee any outcome between the parties.</p>

<h2>5. Bodyshop Account Use</h2>
<p>Registered Bodyshops are responsible for maintaining accurate business profiles. 
  We reserve the right to suspend accounts due to misuse, abuse, or persistent inactivity. 
  Bodyshops must treat all Customer data with confidentiality and comply with UK data protection laws.</p>

<h2>6. Data Privacy</h2>
<p>Use of the platform is governed by our Privacy Policy.
  We process Customer and Bodyshop data in accordance with applicable privacy laws 
  and ensure all third-party services comply with relevant standards.</p>

<h2>7. Intellectual Property</h2>
<p>All platform content, including text, logos, and visuals, are owned or licensed by My Car Quote. 
  No content may be copied, distributed, or reused without written permission.</p>

<h2>8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
<p>We act solely as an intermediary. We are not liable for disputes, losses, or damages arising from Customer-Bodyshop interactions or quotes. 
  All responsibilities and obligations rest solely with the respective parties.</p>

<h2>9. Modifications</h2>
<p>We reserve the right to update these Terms as needed. 
  Changes will be posted with the updated effective date. 
  Continued use of the platform signifies acceptance of the revised terms.</p>

<h2>10. Contact</h2>
<p>For questions, email us at <strong>office@mcquote.co.uk</strong>.</p>

<h2 id="cookies">Cookies Policy</h2>
